40
00:02:18.291 --> 00:02:20.541
{\an8}[Ray] <i>There are memories that shape us.</i>

41
00:02:22.208 --> 00:02:24.208
{\an8}<i>molding us into what we've become.</i>

42
00:02:32.333 --> 00:02:34.541
{\an8}<i>A mosaic of images and feelings</i>

43
00:02:35.125 --> 00:02:37.666
{\an8}<i>that offers some truth
about how we got here.</i>

44
00:02:38.833 --> 00:02:40.625
{\an8}<i>even if details have blurred with time.</i>

45
00:02:40.708 --> 00:02:41.958
{\an8}Sit down.

46
00:02:42.583 --> 00:02:44.750
{\an8}- You know this is all yours?
- [Young Rachel chuckles]

47
00:02:53.125 --> 00:02:56.625
{\an8}[woman]
<i>♪ She's got a smile that it seems to me ♪</i>

48
00:02:56.708 --> 00:03:00.375
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Reminds me of childhood memories ♪</i>
- [Young Rachel coughs]

49
00:03:00.458 --> 00:03:01.500
{\an8}[woman] Mm.

50
00:03:03.916 --> 00:03:05.583
{\an8}What ya lookin' at. man?

51
00:03:07.208 --> 00:03:08.875
{\an8}I'm lookin' at you. woman.

52
00:03:11.250 --> 00:03:12.375
{\an8}[woman sighs]

53
00:03:16.666 --> 00:03:21.375
{\an8}<i>♪ Where everything was fresh
As the bright blue sky ♪</i>

54
00:03:22.208 --> 00:03:24.267
{\an8}- [Young Rachel giggles]
- [woman] <i>♪ Whoa. oh. oh. oh ♪</i>

55
00:03:24.291 --> 00:03:26.541
{\an8}[softly] <i>♪ Sweet child o' mine ♪</i>

56
00:03:26.625 --> 00:03:27.708
{\an8}[Young Rachel laughs]

57
00:03:28.416 --> 00:03:30.833
{\an8}- I love you.
- [Young Rachel] Love you too.

58
00:03:30.916 --> 00:03:32.833
{\an8}[Ray] <i>As the years pass. we realize</i>

59
00:03:32.916 --> 00:03:35.458
{\an8}<i>we are nothing more
than the experiences that made us.</i>

60
00:03:35.541 --> 00:03:38.500
{\an8}<i>♪ Oh. oh. oh. sweet child o' mine ♪</i>

61
00:03:38.583 --> 00:03:40.583
{\an8}- [sirens wailing]
- [Ray exhales heavily]

62
00:03:48.416 --> 00:03:49.791
{\an8}- [doctor] Hi. Amanda.
- Hi.

63
00:03:49.875 --> 00:03:51.235
{\an8}- [Ray] Doc.
- [doctor] Mr. Cooper.

64
00:03:52.291 --> 00:03:53.291
{\an8}Is it back?

65
00:03:54.583 --> 00:03:57.208
{\an8}[doctor] Yes. We'll go over the options.

66
00:03:57.291 --> 00:04:00.791
{\an8}but Infirmam is still the most effective
way to cure this type of cancer.

67
00:04:00.875 --> 00:04:02.708
{\an8}We've already leveraged everything.

68
00:04:02.791 --> 00:04:04.500
{\an8}[monitors beeping]

69
00:04:05.958 --> 00:04:08.208
{\an8}[Ray]
<i>The pain has brought us closer together.</i>

70
00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:13.333
{\an8}<i>And watching her grow…
has been to find myself again.</i>

71
00:04:13.416 --> 00:04:15.166
[all] Surprise!

72
00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:17.333
Here. mama. This is for you.

73
00:04:17.833 --> 00:04:20.625
I mean. it's not much.
but it's all they had at the gift shop.

74
00:04:20.708 --> 00:04:22.208
- Oh.
- [Amanda] Her name is Paloma.

75
00:04:22.291 --> 00:04:24.791
No. it's perfect. Thank you. Mom.

76
00:04:24.875 --> 00:04:26.666
[Ray] <i>But sometimes I wonder.</i>

77
00:04:28.250 --> 00:04:29.666
<i>"Are these </i>my <i>memories.</i>

78
00:04:30.666 --> 00:04:32.291
<i>or are they hers?"</i>

79
00:04:32.375 --> 00:04:34.958
- [men grunting]
- [blows landing]

80
00:04:35.041 --> 00:04:37.708
- [Ray grunting]
- [coach] Put your hips into it. Again.

81
00:04:39.625 --> 00:04:42.250
- [Ray grunts] Ooh.
- [laughs] Ooh. that was clean.

82
00:04:42.333 --> 00:04:44.833
- Lock that wrist so it don't get weak.
- It won't!

83
00:04:44.916 --> 00:04:46.041
[Ray grunts. thuds]

84
00:04:46.125 --> 00:04:48.041
There are no rules in a fight.
people do not...

85
00:04:48.125 --> 00:04:49.583
- Whoa!
- Fight fair!

86
00:04:49.666 --> 00:04:52.125
- [both grunt]
- [Ray] How do you win an unfair fight?

87
00:04:52.208 --> 00:04:53.208
Ah!

88
00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:56.041
- [Rachel] You always fight harder.
- That's right.

89
00:04:56.125 --> 00:04:58.416
[man] Let me train her. Coop.
She's got what it takes.

90
00:04:58.500 --> 00:05:00.333
- That's my sweet girl.
- [laughs]

91
00:05:01.958 --> 00:05:03.625
[monitors beeping]

92
00:05:03.708 --> 00:05:05.458
- [Rachel] Done.
- Done?

93
00:05:05.541 --> 00:05:07.458
[both chuckling]

94
00:05:08.375 --> 00:05:09.625
Thank you. baby.

95
00:05:09.708 --> 00:05:10.708
Go on.

96
00:05:11.958 --> 00:05:12.958
[camera shutter clicks]

97
00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:15.000
[indistinct chatter]

98
00:05:15.083 --> 00:05:17.458
[monitors beeping]

99
00:05:17.541 --> 00:05:19.291
{\an8}[Ray] <i>Parents and their children.</i>

100
00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:22.708
{\an8}<i>Where do we stop and they begin?</i>

101
00:05:24.833 --> 00:05:26.625
Mr. Cooper. Ray.

102
00:05:26.708 --> 00:05:28.708
- Doc.
- I have good news.

103
00:05:28.791 --> 00:05:29.875
We just got word

104
00:05:29.958 --> 00:05:32.916
a very effective generic version
of Infirmam. called Spero.

105
00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:35.500
is in the final stages of FDA approval.

106
00:05:35.583 --> 00:05:36.833
[chuckles]

107
00:05:36.916 --> 00:05:38.875
[softly] This is great news. Ray.

108
00:05:38.958 --> 00:05:40.125
[Rachel chuckles]

109
00:05:41.416 --> 00:05:42.708
Did you do this?

110
00:05:43.583 --> 00:05:45.103
- You did. didn't you?
- [Rachel] What?

111
00:05:45.166 --> 00:05:47.666
This was your birthday wish.
wasn't it? [kisses]

112
00:05:48.166 --> 00:05:50.333
I love you. Let's go tell Mom.

113
00:05:50.416 --> 00:05:52.416
[gentle music continues playing]

114
00:05:57.291 --> 00:05:59.291
- [monitor beeping]
- [machines whirring]

115
00:05:59.375 --> 00:06:01.375
[indistinct chatter in hall]

116
00:06:14.625 --> 00:06:16.500
We were supposed to start
a new medication.

117
00:06:17.833 --> 00:06:19.458
You know when that's supposed to happen?

118
00:06:20.291 --> 00:06:22.583
I… You'll have to talk with Dr. Wu.

119
00:06:29.916 --> 00:06:31.291
[Ray sighs]

120
00:06:36.208 --> 00:06:38.208
[indistinct chatter]

121
00:06:39.125 --> 00:06:40.500
[Rachel] Dad. what's happening?

122
00:06:42.041 --> 00:06:43.041
[Ray] Dr. Wu?

123
00:06:43.750 --> 00:06:44.750
Dr. Wu!

124
00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.250
- [Wu] Hi. Ray.
- What's goin' on?

125
00:06:48.750 --> 00:06:51.000
You said Amanda was
gonna start Spero soon.

126
00:06:51.083 --> 00:06:52.208
I'm sorry.

127
00:06:52.916 --> 00:06:55.166
Amanda's on my list of patients to see.

128
00:06:57.625 --> 00:06:59.833
The company that makes the generic drug

129
00:07:01.333 --> 00:07:03.208
pulled it off the market.

130
00:07:06.083 --> 00:07:07.458
What are you talkin' about?

131
00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:10.958
BioPrime. the makers of Infirmam.

132
00:07:11.041 --> 00:07:13.666
paid the manufacturer
to delay Spero's release.

133
00:07:14.250 --> 00:07:16.583
- Delay?
- For how long?

134
00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:20.500
Indefinitely.

135
00:07:25.875 --> 00:07:26.875
Ray.

136
00:07:26.958 --> 00:07:29.958
You told me
that my wife was gonna be okay.

137
00:07:32.083 --> 00:07:35.291
I am delivering the same news
to three other patients today…

138
00:07:36.416 --> 00:07:37.958
[quietly] …two of them kids.

139
00:07:40.875 --> 00:07:42.291
I am so sorry.

140
00:07:45.500 --> 00:07:46.541
I'm sorry.

141
00:07:54.125 --> 00:07:55.125
[Ray sniffles]

142
00:07:57.625 --> 00:08:00.166
- [monitor beeping]
- [ventilator whirring]

143
00:08:07.416 --> 00:08:09.541
- [news fanfare plays]
- [host] <i>Welcome back.</i>

144
00:08:09.625 --> 00:08:13.291
For those just joining. I'm here
with BioPrime CEO. Simon Keeley.

145
00:08:13.375 --> 00:08:15.958
and Congresswoman
Diana Morgan of Pennsylvania.

146
00:08:16.041 --> 00:08:19.208
Congresswoman Morgan.
why are you here today?

147
00:08:19.291 --> 00:08:22.500
<i>Well. I've always taken a hard line
against pharmaceutical lobbies</i>

148
00:08:22.583 --> 00:08:24.708
<i>and mass corporations. like BioPrime.</i>

149
00:08:24.791 --> 00:08:26.416
With all due respect. Congresswoman.

150
00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:29.791
BioPrime is unlike any other
pharmaceutical company in the world.

151
00:08:29.875 --> 00:08:32.375
- [TV volume raises]
- [Keeley] <i>Our scientists have created</i>

152
00:08:32.458 --> 00:08:36.333
<i>the most effective treatments
in the fight against cancer.</i>

153
00:08:36.416 --> 00:08:40.333
<i>Specifically with Infirmam.
a drug that has increased life expectancy</i>

154
00:08:40.416 --> 00:08:44.083
<i>in 86% of patients treated.</i>

155
00:08:44.166 --> 00:08:46.833
<i>Mr. Keeley. it is not the efficacy
that's in question.</i>

156
00:08:46.916 --> 00:08:49.750
<i>It's the business practices.
It's the company's business practices.</i>

157
00:08:49.833 --> 00:08:52.666
<i>I believe that we all
have a basic human right</i>

158
00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:54.458
{\an8}<i>to safe. affordable medication.</i>

159
00:08:54.541 --> 00:08:59.333
{\an8}<i>Yeah. Um. this talking point
of health care as a human right.</i>

160
00:08:59.416 --> 00:09:03.916
<i>Our medicines.
they are a matter of research and science.</i>

161
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:09.125
{\an8}<i>The investment is not only risky.
it is extremely expensive.</i>

162
00:09:09.208 --> 00:09:12.041
[Langley] <i>All right. We have</i>
<i>eager callers that wanna weigh in.</i>

163
00:09:12.125 --> 00:09:14.750
[caller] <i>Can you please explain?</i>
<i>Because I just don't understand.</i>

164
00:09:14.833 --> 00:09:17.750
<i>It's crazy that a pill can cost that much.</i>

165
00:09:17.833 --> 00:09:20.291
- Yeah. this is. uh. a tricky issue.
- [line ringing]

166
00:09:20.375 --> 00:09:23.416
Uh. and don't get fooled
by the talking points

167
00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:25.333
of… of politicians from Washington.

168
00:09:25.416 --> 00:09:28.541
<i>Mr. Keeley.
according to your own internal documents.</i>

169
00:09:28.625 --> 00:09:31.666
<i>the cost of an entire course
of treatment is only four dollars.</i>

170
00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:35.125
You're absolutely right.
A… A course of treatment <i>is </i>four dollars.

171
00:09:35.208 --> 00:09:38.875
But it's funny how you failed to mention
the billions of dollars spent on…

172
00:09:38.958 --> 00:09:40.500
- [operator] <i>Your name?</i>
- Ray Cooper.

173
00:09:40.583 --> 00:09:43.833
…rebates. discounts.
insurance companies. wholesalers. Look.

174
00:09:43.916 --> 00:09:46.333
{\an8}<i>I'm here because BioPrime</i>

175
00:09:46.416 --> 00:09:49.583
{\an8}<i>is committed to healing the world.</i>

176
00:09:49.666 --> 00:09:52.750
{\an8}<i>And if you look at the numbers.
that is exactly what we're doing.</i>

177
00:09:52.833 --> 00:09:55.166
{\an8}- [scoffs] <i>That is </i>not <i>what you are doing.</i>
<i>- All right.</i>

178
00:09:55.250 --> 00:09:57.458
{\an8}<i>Just to interject.
our next caller is from Pittsburgh.</i>

179
00:09:57.541 --> 00:09:59.791
<i>Ray. do you have something
to say to Mr. Keeley?</i>

180
00:09:59.875 --> 00:10:03.458
My wife is dying in a hospital
because you pulled Spero off the market.

181
00:10:04.291 --> 00:10:07.875
<i>Paying competitors
to shelve generic brands of drugs?</i>

182
00:10:08.375 --> 00:10:10.500
[scoffs] <i>That is immoral. Mr. Keeley.</i>

183
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:12.458
Well… [clears throat]

184
00:10:12.541 --> 00:10:13.625
…Ray…

185
00:10:13.708 --> 00:10:14.875
Is it... Should... Can I?

186
00:10:14.958 --> 00:10:16.875
Uh. I just wanna talk to Ray directly.

187
00:10:16.958 --> 00:10:18.000
<i>Listen.</i>

188
00:10:18.083 --> 00:10:21.208
{\an8}<i>Uh. first of all.
I'd just like to say I'm so sorry</i>

189
00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:22.833
{\an8}<i>to hear about your wife.</i>

190
00:10:22.916 --> 00:10:24.958
<i>Uh. believe it or not.</i>

191
00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:28.250
{\an8}<i>BioPrime is dedicated to </i>saving <i>lives.</i>

192
00:10:29.458 --> 00:10:32.458
Saving lives?
You're geared towards makin' a profit.

193
00:10:32.541 --> 00:10:34.083
We've already refinanced our house.

194
00:10:34.166 --> 00:10:36.000
I've taken every double shift I can get.

195
00:10:36.083 --> 00:10:38.041
You've already taken everything from me!

196
00:10:38.541 --> 00:10:42.041
[Keeley] <i>Ray.</i>
<i>the sad reality is that cancer</i>

197
00:10:42.125 --> 00:10:44.916
is still very often a death sentence.

198
00:10:45.000 --> 00:10:46.000
<i>Uh…</i>

199
00:10:46.041 --> 00:10:48.000
<i>In the short term. what would we give?</i>

200
00:10:48.083 --> 00:10:50.750
[hesitates] <i>What is the cost</i>

201
00:10:50.833 --> 00:10:54.291
<i>of spending just a little bit
more time with a loved one?</i>

202
00:10:54.375 --> 00:10:57.000
A year. a… a month. a day?

203
00:10:57.500 --> 00:11:00.083
Mmm. it's impossible to put a price on.

204
00:11:00.583 --> 00:11:02.583
[tense music playing]

205
00:11:02.666 --> 00:11:04.333
If my wife dies.

206
00:11:04.916 --> 00:11:06.791
<i>it's </i>your <i>death sentence.</i>

207
00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:10.041
I will hunt you down
and kill you with my bare hands.

208
00:11:10.125 --> 00:11:11.125
[Rachel] Dad?

209
00:11:19.833 --> 00:11:20.833
[Ray sighs]

210
00:11:21.500 --> 00:11:23.500
- [monitor beeping]
- [machines whirring]

211
00:11:27.416 --> 00:11:28.833
[Amanda chuckles softly]

212
00:11:29.875 --> 00:11:31.750
[weakly] What ya lookin' at. man?

213
00:11:32.875 --> 00:11:33.958
[Ray chuckles softly]

214
00:11:35.583 --> 00:11:37.666
[softly] I'm lookin' at you. woman.

215
00:11:38.250 --> 00:11:39.250
[Amanda sighs]

216
00:11:41.291 --> 00:11:43.458
[softly] <i>♪ She's got eyes ♪</i>

217
00:11:44.208 --> 00:11:46.666
<i>♪ Of the bluest skies ♪</i>

218
00:11:48.375 --> 00:11:51.250
<i>♪ As if they thought of rain ♪</i>

219
00:11:51.333 --> 00:11:52.791
[Amanda breathing shakily]

220
00:11:52.875 --> 00:11:57.083
<i>♪ I'd hate to look into those eyes ♪</i>

221
00:11:58.083 --> 00:12:00.916
<i>♪ And see an ounce of pain ♪</i>

222
00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:03.541
[Amanda moans weakly. exhales]

223
00:12:10.375 --> 00:12:12.416
[somber music playing]

224
00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:17.041
[voice breaking] <i>♪ Her hair reminds me</i>
<i>Of a warm. safe place ♪</i>

225
00:12:19.125 --> 00:12:23.166
<i>♪ Where as a child. I'd hide ♪</i>

226
00:12:25.625 --> 00:12:27.375
<i>♪ And pray… ♪ </i>[crying]

227
00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:31.250
[sniffles]

228
00:12:35.083 --> 00:12:36.541
[Rachel sobs softly]

229
00:12:37.291 --> 00:12:41.541
<i>♪ And wait for the thunder and the rain ♪</i>

230
00:12:43.041 --> 00:12:45.375
<i>♪ To quietly pass me… ♪</i>

231
00:12:46.666 --> 00:12:48.458
[somber music building]

232
00:12:48.541 --> 00:12:50.541
[Rachel breathing shakily]

233
00:12:59.291 --> 00:13:00.833
[Ray sobs]

234
00:13:06.458 --> 00:13:08.208
[staff chattering indistinctly]

235
00:13:08.958 --> 00:13:10.333
[Ray sobs]

236
00:13:11.666 --> 00:13:13.458
- [sniffles]
- [lights buzzing loudly]

237
00:13:14.458 --> 00:13:16.041
[staff chattering]

238
00:13:18.875 --> 00:13:21.500
[Ray crying softly. sniffles]

239
00:13:22.208 --> 00:13:23.375
Oh God!

240
00:13:25.625 --> 00:13:26.750
Oh my God!

241
00:13:26.833 --> 00:13:28.500
Oh. Amanda!

242
00:13:28.583 --> 00:13:29.583
Oh God!

243
00:13:29.666 --> 00:13:30.750
[continues sobbing]

244
00:13:33.250 --> 00:13:35.083
[sniffles] Oh God!

245
00:13:39.500 --> 00:13:40.583
[shouting] No!

246
00:13:41.375 --> 00:13:43.333
[sobs loudly]

247
00:13:43.416 --> 00:13:45.208
Fuck. no!

248
00:13:45.291 --> 00:13:47.708
Amanda. no!

249
00:13:49.583 --> 00:13:50.458
No!

250
00:13:50.541 --> 00:13:52.541
[continues sobbing and panting]

251
00:13:55.041 --> 00:13:57.041
[somber music fading]

252
00:13:57.833 --> 00:13:58.833
[softly] Bye.

253
00:14:04.291 --> 00:14:06.666
[siren wailing in distance]

254
00:14:06.750 --> 00:14:08.750
["And It's Still Alright" playing]

255
00:14:11.750 --> 00:14:13.500
[Ray grunting]

256
00:14:13.583 --> 00:14:15.625
<i>♪ Now. close your eyes ♪</i>

257
00:14:15.708 --> 00:14:16.916
<i>♪ And spin around ♪</i>

258
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:19.041
<i>♪ Say. hard times ♪</i>

259
00:14:19.125 --> 00:14:23.291
<i>♪ You could find
It ain't the way that you want ♪</i>

260
00:14:27.125 --> 00:14:29.125
<i>♪ But it's alright ♪</i>

261
00:14:29.208 --> 00:14:32.125
[grunting loudly]

262
00:14:33.583 --> 00:14:35.166
[grunting fades slightly]

263
00:14:35.250 --> 00:14:37.375
<i>♪ They say you learn a lot out there ♪</i>

264
00:14:38.583 --> 00:14:40.708
<i>♪ How to scorch and burn ♪</i>

265
00:14:41.500 --> 00:14:44.041
<i>♪ Only have to bury your friends ♪</i>

266
00:14:44.791 --> 00:14:46.666
<i>♪ Then you'll find it gets worse ♪</i>

267
00:14:47.875 --> 00:14:49.708
<i>♪ Standin' out on the ledge ♪</i>

268
00:14:51.041 --> 00:14:54.000
<i>- ♪ With no way to get down ♪</i>
- [Ray takes a deep breath]

269
00:14:54.083 --> 00:14:56.958
<i>♪ You start prayin' for wings to grow ♪</i>

270
00:14:58.208 --> 00:15:03.750
<i>♪ But it's still alright ♪</i>

271
00:15:08.083 --> 00:15:11.375
- [Ray] Ah. God damn it.
- [Rachel] What? Hospital bill?

272
00:15:13.541 --> 00:15:15.625
Just… put it at the bottom of the pile.

273
00:15:15.708 --> 00:15:18.708
- We can't ignore it.
- [Rachel] Sure you can.

274
00:15:18.791 --> 00:15:21.666
- [stove clicks]
- We voted for universal health care. Just…

275
00:15:21.750 --> 00:15:23.750
Tell 'em we're taking a political stance.

276
00:15:23.833 --> 00:15:25.125
[Ray] Hmm.

277
00:15:28.166 --> 00:15:31.083
No. we are not eating that
three nights in a row.

278
00:15:31.166 --> 00:15:33.684
- C'mon. You know you love this too.
- [Ray] It's not happening.

279
00:15:33.708 --> 00:15:36.041
We're gonna order
something with vegetables.

280
00:15:36.125 --> 00:15:38.333
- [Rachel laughing]
- Fries do not count.

281
00:15:38.416 --> 00:15:40.375
- [Rachel] Hey!
- No. Stop.

282
00:15:41.041 --> 00:15:43.833
- Ah! Stop ticklin' me.
- [cell phone vibrates]

283
00:15:43.916 --> 00:15:46.041
[Ray chuckles] Stop it.

284
00:15:46.125 --> 00:15:47.875
- Hello?
- [man on phone] <i>Ray Cooper?</i>

285
00:15:48.500 --> 00:15:51.250
<i>My name is Martin Bennett.</i>
<i>I'm a journalist for </i>VICE.

286
00:15:51.333 --> 00:15:55.291
<i>I'm doing a story on BioPrime. and
I saw your call with Simon Keeley on TV.</i>

287
00:15:56.083 --> 00:15:57.250
[Ray] What do you want?

288
00:15:57.333 --> 00:16:00.166
<i>I can help you get justice
for what happened to your wife.</i>

289
00:16:01.250 --> 00:16:03.708
No. you can't. I've been down that road.

290
00:16:04.333 --> 00:16:06.541
<i>I have proof
that crimes have been committed.</i>

291
00:16:07.083 --> 00:16:09.958
<i>Crimes that can land
some very powerful people in jail.</i>

292
00:16:10.833 --> 00:16:12.458
- Keeley?
- Who's that?

293
00:16:12.541 --> 00:16:15.375
<i>Especially Keeley.
We need to talk in person.</i>

294
00:16:17.333 --> 00:16:20.583
- You can talk now. Now you have me.
- <i>Not over the phone.</i>

295
00:16:20.666 --> 00:16:24.000
<i>Meet me at Gateway Station in 20 minutes.
I won't waste your time.</i>

296
00:16:24.083 --> 00:16:26.833
- [call disconnects]
- [Rachel] Who was that?

297
00:16:27.666 --> 00:16:29.208
[Ray] I'll be right back.

298
00:16:29.708 --> 00:16:31.916
What do you want? Chinese or Subway?

299
00:16:32.833 --> 00:16:33.833
[menus thud]

300
00:16:35.291 --> 00:16:38.083
No. it's cool. I'll come with you.
and we can pick it up on the way.

301
00:16:38.166 --> 00:16:40.541
Not gonna happen. Rae.
Sit there and finish that homework.

302
00:16:41.041 --> 00:16:42.375
[Rachel] That's not fair.

303
00:16:42.458 --> 00:16:43.958
Life's not fair.

304
00:16:47.125 --> 00:16:48.250
Chinese?

305
00:16:49.166 --> 00:16:51.125
Lock the door behind me.

306
00:16:51.208 --> 00:16:53.708
- I love you.
- Love you. [sighs]

307
00:16:53.791 --> 00:16:55.291
[tense music playing]

308
00:16:55.375 --> 00:16:57.375
[indistinct chatter]

309
00:17:10.583 --> 00:17:11.916
[Ray] Excuse me.

310
00:17:15.291 --> 00:17:17.291
[train approaching]

311
00:17:22.083 --> 00:17:23.583
[cell phone vibrating]

312
00:17:26.166 --> 00:17:28.083
Yeah. I'm here. Where are you?

313
00:17:28.166 --> 00:17:31.458
- [Bennett] <i>Get on the incoming train.</i>
- [Ray] You were supposed to meet me here.

314
00:17:31.541 --> 00:17:33.458
<i>Trust me. Ray. Just get on the train.</i>

315
00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:45.083
<i>Are you on the train?</i>

316
00:17:45.166 --> 00:17:48.500
- Yeah. Now what?
- <i>Don't hang up. Just stay on the line.</i>

317
00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:51.750
<i>Just sit tight.</i>

318
00:17:53.708 --> 00:17:55.166
<i>Get off at this station.</i>

319
00:18:04.666 --> 00:18:06.000
Okay. where now?

320
00:18:06.083 --> 00:18:08.875
<i>There's a woman in a striped coat
and a hipster guy with a scarf.</i>

321
00:18:08.958 --> 00:18:11.500
<i>- You see where they're headed?</i>
- Yeah. To street level.

322
00:18:12.375 --> 00:18:15.750
<i>All right. There's a guy in a denim jacket
going up the stairs.</i>

323
00:18:15.833 --> 00:18:19.375
<i>I want you to follow that guy.
Hang back. but don't lose him.</i>

324
00:18:29.250 --> 00:18:30.541
<i>Stand by.</i>

325
00:18:30.625 --> 00:18:32.500
[indistinct chatter]

326
00:18:33.083 --> 00:18:35.000
<i>Head to the south platform</i>

327
00:18:35.083 --> 00:18:37.916
and take the Red Line
towards Allegheny Station. Okay?

328
00:18:42.291 --> 00:18:43.791
<i>Stay on the line.</i>

329
00:19:01.666 --> 00:19:04.541
- Bennett?
- Yeah. Martin.

330
00:19:04.625 --> 00:19:07.500
Look. sorry about all this train hopping.
but it's just a precaution.

331
00:19:09.708 --> 00:19:10.875
Okay. honestly.

332
00:19:11.791 --> 00:19:14.083
I'm a little afraid of
how deep this thing might go.

333
00:19:14.166 --> 00:19:15.250
What does that mean?

334
00:19:15.333 --> 00:19:18.083
I got a source who told me
about BioPrime's payouts

335
00:19:18.166 --> 00:19:20.541
to multiple offshore shell corporations.

336
00:19:20.625 --> 00:19:24.875
Bribery. cover-ups. who knows what else.
All this leads to Simon Keeley.

337
00:19:26.916 --> 00:19:30.041
There are other players
at both the state and federal level.

338
00:19:30.708 --> 00:19:33.291
But recently. communication went silent.

339
00:19:34.000 --> 00:19:35.291
You told me you had proof.

340
00:19:35.375 --> 00:19:38.541
[Bennett] Enough to tie Keeley to bribes
that pulled Spero off the market.

341
00:19:38.625 --> 00:19:40.505
But without my source.
I can't connect the dots.

342
00:19:40.541 --> 00:19:41.833
You're wastin' my time.

343
00:19:41.916 --> 00:19:44.541
[Bennett] I have enough
to bring public concern against BioPrime.

344
00:19:44.625 --> 00:19:47.000
but I do not have enough
to take them down.

345
00:19:47.083 --> 00:19:49.500
That's why I need you. your story.

346
00:19:49.583 --> 00:19:51.416
- I just...
- Look. just think about it.

347
00:19:51.500 --> 00:19:55.083
Look. "Local family gets ravaged
by Big Pharma's greed."

348
00:19:55.166 --> 00:19:56.458
[brakes screech]

349
00:19:56.541 --> 00:19:58.250
[Bennett] You gotta help me. Ray.

350
00:19:58.750 --> 00:20:01.208
Family. human interest.
That's what grabs headlines.

351
00:20:01.291 --> 00:20:02.916
We can blow this thing wide open.

352
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:06.500
We can take down BioPrime.
We can bring Simon Keeley to his knees.

353
00:20:06.583 --> 00:20:07.791
[gasps]

354
00:20:08.291 --> 00:20:10.166
[suspenseful music playing]

355
00:20:10.250 --> 00:20:11.625
- Hey!
- [blade swishes]

356
00:20:12.875 --> 00:20:14.250
Dad!

357
00:20:15.250 --> 00:20:16.458
Run!

358
00:20:17.375 --> 00:20:18.833
[Ray and hit man grunting]

359
00:20:30.375 --> 00:20:31.375
Hey!

360
00:20:34.541 --> 00:20:37.000
- [groans. screams]
- [Ray grunts]

361
00:20:42.083 --> 00:20:43.916
- [Ray yells]
- [hit man groans]

362
00:20:48.333 --> 00:20:49.416
[Ray yells]

363
00:20:53.166 --> 00:20:54.708
- [hit man shouts]
- [Ray thuds]

364
00:20:55.250 --> 00:20:56.250
[Rachel grunts]

365
00:20:56.916 --> 00:20:58.083
[hit man groans]

366
00:20:59.666 --> 00:21:01.083
[Rachel yelps]

367
00:21:01.583 --> 00:21:02.916
[groans]

368
00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:04.750
- [Ray yells]
- [hit man groaning]

369
00:21:13.541 --> 00:21:15.166
[Ray cries out]

370
00:21:17.250 --> 00:21:19.250
[panting]

371
00:21:19.333 --> 00:21:21.333
[music fades]

372
00:21:23.291 --> 00:21:24.916
[groans] Rachel.

373
00:21:25.000 --> 00:21:27.208
Rachel. baby. are you okay? Look at me.

374
00:21:27.708 --> 00:21:31.500
- [suspenseful music swells]
- [Ray screaming. muffled]

375
00:21:36.583 --> 00:21:37.708
[moans weakly]

376
00:21:43.541 --> 00:21:45.541
[train rattling on tracks]

377
00:21:51.250 --> 00:21:53.166
[speaking inaudibly]

378
00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:19.291
[music fades]

379
00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:23.000
[Rachel grunting]

380
00:22:33.750 --> 00:22:36.375
[grunting rapidly]

381
00:22:38.708 --> 00:22:40.708
[panting]

382
00:22:45.083 --> 00:22:47.166
- [coach] Just like your dad.
- [Rachel grunting]

383
00:22:47.250 --> 00:22:49.750
- Not about strength.
- [both grunting]

384
00:22:49.833 --> 00:22:52.583
Okay. top. Top. Up. up. up!

385
00:22:53.583 --> 00:22:55.083
Hands up. Hands up. Move.

386
00:22:58.166 --> 00:23:00.666
Again. Hit him again.
Control him. Let's go.

387
00:23:01.916 --> 00:23:03.708
Come on. You can take anyone.

388
00:23:05.041 --> 00:23:06.583
Beautiful. There it is.

389
00:23:09.333 --> 00:23:11.708
Nice. Top. top. top. top!
Watch the scramble.

390
00:23:11.791 --> 00:23:12.791
All right.

391
00:23:13.416 --> 00:23:15.791
Hooks in. Get it. Get him in. Here.

392
00:23:15.875 --> 00:23:17.291
Pick your shots.

393
00:23:18.166 --> 00:23:19.458
That's it. Open him up.

394
00:23:19.541 --> 00:23:21.916
- [both grunt]
- [coach] You got it. Lock it in.

395
00:23:22.583 --> 00:23:23.791
Beautiful.

396
00:23:23.875 --> 00:23:25.458
Just hold. Hold. hold.

397
00:23:25.541 --> 00:23:27.583
[both grunting]

398
00:23:27.666 --> 00:23:28.666
[choking]

399
00:23:29.416 --> 00:23:30.875
[coach] He's tapping. Rachel.

400
00:23:30.958 --> 00:23:32.458
Rachel. he's tapping.

401
00:23:32.541 --> 00:23:35.375
- He's tapping. Rachel. Rachel!
- [sounds fading]

402
00:23:35.458 --> 00:23:36.750
[high-pitched ringing]

403
00:23:36.833 --> 00:23:37.833
[coach] Rachel!

404
00:23:37.875 --> 00:23:39.666
[Rachel panting]

405
00:23:39.750 --> 00:23:40.750
[coach] Rachel!

406
00:23:40.833 --> 00:23:42.666
- [ringing stops]
- [opponent coughing]

407
00:23:43.291 --> 00:23:45.875
- [Rachel panting]
- [opponent gasping for air]

408
00:23:45.958 --> 00:23:48.416
[somber music playing]

409
00:23:54.583 --> 00:23:58.041
- [birds singing]
- [sirens wailing in distance]

410
00:23:58.125 --> 00:24:01.125
Today. I am thrilled
to announce a bipartisan bill

411
00:24:01.208 --> 00:24:05.458
that will make true progress
in the war to find a cure for cancer.

412
00:24:05.958 --> 00:24:09.166
In collaboration with the CDC and the NIH.

413
00:24:09.250 --> 00:24:11.583
we are creating a strategic partnership

414
00:24:11.666 --> 00:24:13.750
with BioPrime Pharmaceuticals.

415
00:24:13.833 --> 00:24:17.166
Thanks to the effort
of BioPrime CEO. Simon Keeley.

416
00:24:17.250 --> 00:24:19.000
and chairman. Vinod Shah.

417
00:24:19.083 --> 00:24:23.041
this bill will effectively cap
the cost of treatment.

418
00:24:23.666 --> 00:24:27.166
{\an8}<i>Finally. many of BioPrime's
breakthrough treatments</i>

419
00:24:27.250 --> 00:24:30.333
<i>that used to cost
in the hundreds of thousands of dollars</i>

420
00:24:30.416 --> 00:24:34.375
<i>will now be available
to the public at affordable prices.</i>

421
00:24:34.875 --> 00:24:36.208
<i>I told the American people</i>

422
00:24:36.291 --> 00:24:39.291
<i>that I would hold companies
like BioPrime accountable.</i>

423
00:24:39.375 --> 00:24:41.666
<i>and I have delivered on that promise.</i>

424
00:24:42.208 --> 00:24:44.791
<i>We are cleaning out the rot.</i>

425
00:24:44.875 --> 00:24:46.916
- [reporters clamoring on TV]
<i>- Yes?</i>

426
00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:49.916
- [reporter] <i>Are you planning on running...</i>
- [TV turns off]

427
00:24:51.291 --> 00:24:52.375
[Ray] Again?

428
00:24:54.958 --> 00:24:57.000
I wasn't watching it. You were.

429
00:25:00.041 --> 00:25:01.750
I had a dream last night

430
00:25:01.833 --> 00:25:04.583
about that trip we took
with Mom in the woods.

431
00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:10.041
My memory's kind of fading of her.

432
00:25:11.333 --> 00:25:15.416
I don't know. It's like I'm losing these
tiny pieces of her every day. and I just…

433
00:25:17.916 --> 00:25:20.000
I don't know.
I miss her. I miss our family.

434
00:25:21.458 --> 00:25:22.583
Me too.

435
00:25:27.416 --> 00:25:28.750
I miss her too.

436
00:25:40.750 --> 00:25:42.583
What are you planning to do?

437
00:25:43.458 --> 00:25:45.250
I just need to make sense of this.

438
00:25:46.958 --> 00:25:51.208
- I need to know.
- Just… Just leave it alone. okay?

439
00:25:52.208 --> 00:25:54.750
They already investigated.
and they didn't find anything.

440
00:25:54.833 --> 00:25:57.000
Or the guy who tried to kill you.

441
00:25:57.500 --> 00:25:59.333
It just was a dead-end conspiracy.

442
00:26:00.041 --> 00:26:01.250
[Ray sighs]

443
00:26:01.333 --> 00:26:03.375
- I don't believe that.
- [Rachel sighs]

444
00:26:04.708 --> 00:26:06.083
<i>You </i>don't believe that.

445
00:26:08.583 --> 00:26:09.958
I need to try.

446
00:26:16.166 --> 00:26:18.208
[tense music playing]

447
00:26:18.291 --> 00:26:21.166
- [excited chatter]
- [camera shutters clicking]

448
00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:36.041
Keep it close. Mike.

449
00:26:36.125 --> 00:26:38.291
- I don't know how long I'll be.
- [Mike] Yes. sir.

450
00:27:06.541 --> 00:27:07.666
[Keeley sighs]

451
00:27:08.166 --> 00:27:09.750
- Mr. Keeley.
- Ah.

452
00:27:11.125 --> 00:27:12.208
Appreciate it.

453
00:27:12.291 --> 00:27:14.958
- Don't let me go dry tonight. will you?
- [server chuckles]

454
00:27:21.375 --> 00:27:22.833
[announcer] <i>Good evening.</i>

455
00:27:22.916 --> 00:27:25.208
<i>I'm proud to kick off
this first annual event</i>

456
00:27:25.291 --> 00:27:28.166
by introducing you to the CEO of BioPrime.

457
00:27:28.250 --> 00:27:30.166
Mr. Simon Keeley.

458
00:27:30.666 --> 00:27:33.125
- [guests applaud]
- [Keeley clears throat]

459
00:27:33.208 --> 00:27:34.625
[man] Nice to see you. Simon.

460
00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:38.666
Thank you.

461
00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:42.250
Thank you very much. Hello. everyone.

462
00:27:43.625 --> 00:27:45.333
T. S. Eliot said.

463
00:27:45.416 --> 00:27:48.666
"We shall not cease in exploration."

464
00:27:48.750 --> 00:27:50.500
[plates clattering]

465
00:27:50.583 --> 00:27:53.291
[Keeley continues speaking indistinctly]

466
00:27:54.166 --> 00:27:58.625
We've joined forces
with Goa Capital Partners

467
00:27:58.708 --> 00:28:02.166
in hopes of raising ten million dollars…

468
00:28:02.250 --> 00:28:03.083
[guests clap]

469
00:28:03.166 --> 00:28:05.875
For... That's right. I know you got it.

470
00:28:05.958 --> 00:28:07.000
[guests laugh]

471
00:28:07.083 --> 00:28:08.250
Excuse me.

472
00:28:10.916 --> 00:28:11.791
[lock clicks]

473
00:28:11.875 --> 00:28:14.666
[Keeley. over speakers]
<i>For medicine and assistance…</i>

474
00:28:14.750 --> 00:28:16.625
For children in Africa.

475
00:28:16.708 --> 00:28:18.833
India. Sorry. [laughs awkwardly]

476
00:28:18.916 --> 00:28:20.083
[chuckles]

477
00:28:21.916 --> 00:28:25.333
Either way.
both places need a lot of help.

478
00:28:25.416 --> 00:28:27.583
- Thanks again for coming.
- [guests clap]

479
00:28:27.666 --> 00:28:29.666
[murmuring]

480
00:28:31.250 --> 00:28:33.916
Ladies and gentlemen. Mr. Simon Keeley.

481
00:28:35.666 --> 00:28:37.208
[guests chattering]

482
00:28:37.291 --> 00:28:40.541
[lively instrumental music playing]

483
00:28:41.166 --> 00:28:43.458
[Keeley speaking indistinctly]

484
00:29:02.583 --> 00:29:04.166
Simon. Simon. Simon.

485
00:29:04.250 --> 00:29:06.208
India. Africa? Africa. India?

486
00:29:06.291 --> 00:29:08.250
- Hmm?
- [Keeley laughs]

487
00:29:08.333 --> 00:29:12.291
You know what?
I am so sick of doing your job for ya.

488
00:29:12.375 --> 00:29:14.750
I'm doing my job. Simon.
Everyone's here because of me.

489
00:29:14.833 --> 00:29:17.041
There's some important people here.

490
00:29:17.125 --> 00:29:19.458
Might want to mingle
with more than your cocktails.

491
00:29:19.541 --> 00:29:21.375
Sure. all right. Good to see ya.

492
00:29:40.333 --> 00:29:42.166
- [drink spills]
- What the fuck?

493
00:29:44.958 --> 00:29:45.958
Who would…?

494
00:29:48.958 --> 00:29:52.083
- [bodyguard 1] Sir?
- [Keeley] You kidding? Give me a napkin.

495
00:29:52.166 --> 00:29:55.666
…why I agree to participate
in this bullshit in the first place.

496
00:29:55.750 --> 00:29:58.916
- [auctioneer] <i>Let's start the auction.</i>
- Fucking balls are wet.

497
00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:02.625
- [bodyguard 2] It's out of order.
- No shit. How'd you figure that out?

498
00:30:02.708 --> 00:30:05.083
Sir. Sir. there's another bathroom
down the stairs.

499
00:30:05.166 --> 00:30:08.083
[Keeley]
Well. let's go to it. then. All right?

500
00:30:08.166 --> 00:30:10.375
[auctioneer calling bids]

501
00:30:10.458 --> 00:30:12.416
Wait here. Keep a lookout.

502
00:30:14.208 --> 00:30:16.008
- [extinguisher hisses]
- [bodyguard 1 grunts]

503
00:30:18.166 --> 00:30:20.291
- [grunts]
- [extinguisher clangs]

504
00:30:20.375 --> 00:30:22.041
[bodyguard 2 groans]

505
00:30:22.666 --> 00:30:24.291
- [Keeley] Hey. hey. hey!
- [Ray grunts]

506
00:30:24.375 --> 00:30:26.541
- [Keeley groans]
- [blade swishes]

507
00:30:26.625 --> 00:30:28.291
[both grunt]

508
00:30:28.375 --> 00:30:30.625
- [Ray] Hmm?
- What the… fuck?

509
00:30:30.708 --> 00:30:32.083
You were warned.

510
00:30:33.166 --> 00:30:35.416
If anything happened to her.
I would hunt you down.

511
00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:36.500
[Keeley panting]

512
00:30:37.208 --> 00:30:39.958
All made her suffer.
but she died because of you.

513
00:30:40.041 --> 00:30:43.041
I didn't kill anyone. you psycho fuck.
Cancer did.

514
00:30:43.125 --> 00:30:45.125
You paid someone to kill Martin Bennett.

515
00:30:45.708 --> 00:30:48.125
- What? Martin?
- He was investigating your bribes.

516
00:30:48.208 --> 00:30:51.500
What the… What are you talking about?
I don't know any Martin Bennett.

517
00:30:51.583 --> 00:30:54.250
- You're the goddamn CEO of BioPrime.
- All right.

518
00:30:54.333 --> 00:30:58.125
I authorize a bribe now and again.
but it's not like I read the fine print.

519
00:30:58.208 --> 00:30:59.875
[yelling] Okay. now. stop! Stop!

520
00:30:59.958 --> 00:31:01.416
Fuck!

521
00:31:01.916 --> 00:31:03.916
All right. Uh… [grunts]

522
00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:06.750
It must have been Vinod Shah. Okay?

523
00:31:07.625 --> 00:31:12.041
Nothing happens without his sign-off.
He's the one that brought me on. okay?

524
00:31:14.916 --> 00:31:16.833
You have no idea what you're getting into.

525
00:31:16.916 --> 00:31:18.500
- [Ray grunts]
- [Keeley groans]

526
00:31:19.416 --> 00:31:21.500
[Ray and bodyguard 2 grunting]

527
00:31:22.458 --> 00:31:23.458
[Ray groans]

528
00:31:24.000 --> 00:31:25.166
[Keeley screams]

529
00:31:25.916 --> 00:31:27.791
- Get him.
- [tense music playing]

530
00:31:27.875 --> 00:31:29.250
- [Ray groans]
- [Keeley] Hey!

531
00:31:30.250 --> 00:31:32.500
Here. Handle it. Do it!

532
00:31:32.583 --> 00:31:35.083
- [blade slashes]
- [bodyguard 2 screams] Fuck!

533
00:31:35.166 --> 00:31:36.208
No!

534
00:31:36.291 --> 00:31:37.708
[both grunting]

535
00:31:40.750 --> 00:31:41.875
[bodyguard 2 groans]

536
00:31:44.333 --> 00:31:46.250
- [Ray strains]
- [bodyguard 2 moans]

537
00:31:46.875 --> 00:31:48.250
[yells]

538
00:31:48.333 --> 00:31:50.416
- [Keeley] Oh shit!
- [Ray grunts]

539
00:31:50.500 --> 00:31:52.125
[gun fires]

540
00:31:53.083 --> 00:31:55.083
[Keeley and Ray straining]

541
00:31:55.666 --> 00:31:56.875
[gun clatters]

542
00:31:57.708 --> 00:31:58.958
[Ray groans]

543
00:31:59.041 --> 00:32:00.541
Come here. you little bitch!

544
00:32:00.625 --> 00:32:01.708
[Ray shouts]

545
00:32:01.791 --> 00:32:02.875
[both grunting]

546
00:32:06.250 --> 00:32:08.916
[Keeley choking and grunting]

547
00:32:22.625 --> 00:32:25.666
[Keeley crying out]

548
00:32:25.750 --> 00:32:28.500
[screams. gasps]

549
00:32:28.583 --> 00:32:30.041
[yelling stops]

550
00:32:30.125 --> 00:32:31.666
[Ray exhales]

551
00:32:31.750 --> 00:32:33.750
[music fades]

552
00:32:37.458 --> 00:32:38.833
[Keeley thuds]

553
00:32:40.750 --> 00:32:42.833
[panting]

554
00:32:42.916 --> 00:32:44.958
[auctioneer continues calling bids]

555
00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:52.500
- [Ray exhales shakily]
- [auctioneer] <i>Sold! 50.000 dollars.</i>

556
00:32:52.583 --> 00:32:54.583
[guests applaud]

557
00:32:54.666 --> 00:32:56.666
[somber instrumental music playing]

558
00:32:58.375 --> 00:32:59.583
[keys jingle]

559
00:33:00.750 --> 00:33:02.250
[lock clatters]

560
00:33:05.041 --> 00:33:06.041
Rae?

561
00:33:08.541 --> 00:33:09.666
Rachel.

562
00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:14.500
Rachel.

563
00:33:15.666 --> 00:33:17.833
[Rachel] Dad? You're hurt.

564
00:33:18.333 --> 00:33:21.291
[Ray] I'm fine. I need you to pack up.
Only what we need.

565
00:33:22.375 --> 00:33:24.666
- [Rachel] When are we coming back?
- [Ray] We're not.

566
00:33:24.750 --> 00:33:26.166
[faucet squeaks off]

567
00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:27.250
Is that his blood?

568
00:33:29.041 --> 00:33:31.375
I… I had no choice. He had a gun.

569
00:33:33.125 --> 00:33:35.583
I told you not to do this.

570
00:33:40.458 --> 00:33:42.833
People are gonna come after us.
aren't they?

571
00:33:43.333 --> 00:33:44.541
[Ray] I don't know.

572
00:33:46.916 --> 00:33:49.625
But we need to go.
Please go pack our stuff.

573
00:33:51.583 --> 00:33:52.583
[Rachel sighs]

574
00:33:55.416 --> 00:33:56.625
[loudly] Go pack!

575
00:34:06.041 --> 00:34:07.125
[Ray sighs deeply]

576
00:34:07.208 --> 00:34:09.208
[siren wailing]

577
00:34:12.458 --> 00:34:15.708
- [police sirens blaring]
- [helicopter blades whirring overhead]

578
00:34:15.791 --> 00:34:17.791
[indistinct chatter]

579
00:34:25.166 --> 00:34:28.333
Mr. Asbury.
I'm Special Agent Sarah Meeker.

580
00:34:30.166 --> 00:34:31.791
I already gave a statement.

581
00:34:33.250 --> 00:34:35.916
[Meeker] Your partner.
he took a bullet to the head tonight.

582
00:34:37.791 --> 00:34:39.333
Did you hear any gunshots?

583
00:34:40.333 --> 00:34:41.541
[Asbury] No.

584
00:34:41.625 --> 00:34:44.958
Did you hear anything at all
before losing consciousness?

585
00:34:46.958 --> 00:34:48.583
Somethin' about a woman.

586
00:34:50.750 --> 00:34:51.750
Said. uh…

587
00:34:52.708 --> 00:34:54.375
"All of them made her suffer."

588
00:34:54.458 --> 00:34:59.333
- Or… "All made her suffer." I don't know.
- What do you mean? All what? All who?

589
00:35:01.208 --> 00:35:02.916
- I don't know.
- Okay.

590
00:35:03.583 --> 00:35:06.166
- Do you remember anything else?
- No.

591
00:35:06.250 --> 00:35:08.416
- [Asbury sighs]
- Thank you.

592
00:35:09.875 --> 00:35:10.958
Come on.

593
00:35:12.166 --> 00:35:13.458
But wait.

594
00:35:20.291 --> 00:35:23.500
Whoever it was said they warned him.

595
00:35:25.333 --> 00:35:28.666
They said they'd come for Mr. Keeley
if anything happened to the woman.

596
00:35:33.750 --> 00:35:35.666
All right. Thank you.

597
00:35:36.416 --> 00:35:39.375
Let's do a check on all death threats
Keeley may have gotten in the past.

598
00:35:39.458 --> 00:35:40.333
[agent] You got it.

599
00:35:40.416 --> 00:35:42.416
["Day After Tomorrow" playing]

600
00:35:45.791 --> 00:35:49.916
<i>♪ Tell me. how does God choose… ♪</i>

601
00:35:50.000 --> 00:35:52.666
[Ray] It's a long drive to Toronto
on these back roads.

602
00:35:54.083 --> 00:35:55.750
Especially if we're not talking.

603
00:35:55.833 --> 00:35:58.708
<i>♪ Who turns the wheel ♪</i>

604
00:35:59.208 --> 00:36:02.708
<i>- ♪ Who throws the dice ♪</i>
- You gonna come sit up here?

605
00:36:02.791 --> 00:36:07.250
<i>♪ On the day after tomorrow? ♪</i>

606
00:36:11.333 --> 00:36:13.666
[Rachel grunts softly] Talk to Paloma.

607
00:36:13.750 --> 00:36:17.708
<i>♪ I am not fighting for justice ♪</i>

608
00:36:17.791 --> 00:36:20.166
<i>♪ I am fighting ♪</i>

609
00:36:20.250 --> 00:36:22.083
<i>♪ For my life ♪</i>

610
00:36:23.208 --> 00:36:27.166
<i>♪ And another day in the world ♪</i>

611
00:36:27.750 --> 00:36:30.916
We ran all the Keeley death threats.
and we got a match.

612
00:36:31.416 --> 00:36:33.250
Her name is Amanda Cooper.

613
00:36:33.333 --> 00:36:35.500
Died at Carnegie Medical a few years back.

614
00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:38.541
Her husband's Oldsmobile
was at the auction.

615
00:36:38.625 --> 00:36:40.000
And we found this too.

616
00:36:40.625 --> 00:36:42.291
[typing]

617
00:36:42.375 --> 00:36:44.125
[Keeley]
<i>It's impossible to put a price on.</i>

618
00:36:44.208 --> 00:36:47.458
[Ray] <i>If my wife dies.</i>
<i>it's </i>your <i>death sentence.</i>

619
00:36:47.541 --> 00:36:50.208
<i>I will hunt you down
and kill you with my bare hands.</i>

620
00:36:50.291 --> 00:36:53.142
- [Langley] <i>We're gonna take...</i>
- [Meeker hits key] "All made her suffer"?

621
00:36:53.166 --> 00:36:55.041
- Right. [chuckles]
- [Meeker exhales]

622
00:36:56.041 --> 00:36:58.791
Let's put an APB out on Cooper's vehicle.

623
00:36:58.875 --> 00:37:00.875
[somber orchestral music playing]

624
00:37:15.916 --> 00:37:17.166
[attendant] Here you are.

625
00:37:20.416 --> 00:37:23.416
[engine rattling on recording]

626
00:37:23.500 --> 00:37:25.166
[engine revs]

627
00:37:29.750 --> 00:37:31.416
[man] Got the ID on the driver.

628
00:37:35.166 --> 00:37:36.166
[quietly] Yeah.

629
00:37:37.125 --> 00:37:38.875
How do you wanna handle this?

630
00:37:56.125 --> 00:37:57.500
[bell dings]

631
00:38:06.458 --> 00:38:08.583
[bells jingle]

632
00:38:10.791 --> 00:38:12.083
[Ray] Evening.

633
00:38:25.375 --> 00:38:26.916
[engine cuts out]

634
00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:32.083
[keys jingling]

635
00:38:33.666 --> 00:38:34.833
[Ray] I'll be right up.

636
00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:41.833
- [phone rings]
- This is Meeker.

637
00:38:42.333 --> 00:38:45.541
[Rachel] <i>You're the agent assigned</i>
<i>to what happened at the UNICEF fundraiser.</i>

638
00:38:45.625 --> 00:38:48.833
If you have any information.
please call the tip line.

639
00:38:48.916 --> 00:38:51.958
- An agent will get back to you.
<i>- Yeah. I called the tip line.</i>

640
00:38:52.041 --> 00:38:55.791
<i>- I told them I'm only talkin' to you.</i>
- And who am I speaking to?

641
00:38:56.833 --> 00:38:58.958
<i>Simon Keeley's death was an accident.</i>

642
00:38:59.541 --> 00:39:03.083
<i>- It was self-defense.</i>
- How do you know that? Who is this?

643
00:39:03.916 --> 00:39:05.875
I'm gonna tell you
everything that happened.

644
00:39:06.833 --> 00:39:08.500
If you want a crime. look at…

645
00:39:10.166 --> 00:39:11.583
look at what Keeley did.

646
00:39:12.291 --> 00:39:15.916
How many cancer patients died
because of him? Thousands? More?

647
00:39:17.166 --> 00:39:18.666
Where are you. Rachel?

648
00:39:18.750 --> 00:39:21.333
- Goodbye.
- <i>Wait. I can help you.</i>

649
00:39:25.875 --> 00:39:26.875
Um…

650
00:39:27.666 --> 00:39:29.708
My dad doesn't know I'm doing this.

651
00:39:31.333 --> 00:39:32.625
He's a good man. He…

652
00:39:33.208 --> 00:39:34.458
<i>He just needs help.</i>

653
00:39:35.375 --> 00:39:36.583
Do <i>you </i>need help?

654
00:39:36.666 --> 00:39:38.166
[neon light buzzing]

655
00:39:38.250 --> 00:39:39.458
I'm fine.

656
00:39:40.875 --> 00:39:42.166
[somber music playing]

657
00:39:42.250 --> 00:39:44.541
But I know you think he's guilty.

658
00:39:45.791 --> 00:39:47.333
You've all made up your minds.

659
00:39:47.958 --> 00:39:49.125
<i>But you're wrong.</i>

660
00:39:49.208 --> 00:39:51.250
<i>He's a good. honest man.</i>

661
00:39:51.875 --> 00:39:53.500
<i>And I… need him.</i>

662
00:39:58.083 --> 00:39:59.291
He's all I got.

663
00:40:04.208 --> 00:40:05.541
Do you have cash?

664
00:40:06.333 --> 00:40:07.458
<i>Why?</i>

665
00:40:08.791 --> 00:40:13.291
When you can. get to a…
a gas station or a Walmart.

666
00:40:13.375 --> 00:40:15.666
<i>They have disposable phones. a burner.</i>

667
00:40:16.291 --> 00:40:18.375
Okay? You get one. and you call me back.

668
00:40:18.458 --> 00:40:22.958
My number is 412-046-4378.

669
00:40:23.875 --> 00:40:26.416
Okay? No one will be able to trace it.
Okay? It's safe.

670
00:40:26.916 --> 00:40:30.791
<i>Now say it back to me. It's 412-046-4...</i>

671
00:40:31.291 --> 00:40:33.166
- [call disconnects]
- [quietly] Fuck.

672
00:40:46.041 --> 00:40:47.083
[keys jangle]

673
00:40:59.583 --> 00:41:01.583
[bells jingling softly]

674
00:41:18.041 --> 00:41:19.291
[door opens]

675
00:41:24.208 --> 00:41:25.583
Where'd you get that?

676
00:41:29.666 --> 00:41:31.125
Did you steal that?

677
00:41:32.416 --> 00:41:33.958
I'm just looking at it.

678
00:41:35.541 --> 00:41:36.875
It's fine.

679
00:41:37.375 --> 00:41:40.041
What? It's not like
business is booming down there.

680
00:41:40.125 --> 00:41:42.458
- Twenty dollars? Seriously?
- [Rachel sighs]

681
00:41:42.541 --> 00:41:43.791
We're not done.

682
00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:46.125
[Rachel exhales]

683
00:41:47.083 --> 00:41:50.333
Look. I know you've always taught me
to do the right thing. okay?

684
00:41:50.416 --> 00:41:52.208
But we're here because of you.

685
00:41:52.291 --> 00:41:53.708
[door slams. locks]

686
00:41:53.791 --> 00:41:54.833
[Rachel sighs]

687
00:42:39.958 --> 00:42:41.375
[bells jingle]

688
00:42:41.458 --> 00:42:42.958
[suspenseful music playing]

689
00:42:49.666 --> 00:42:50.666
[Rachel] Hmm?

690
00:42:50.750 --> 00:42:53.083
Rachel. look at me.
Look at me. We gotta go.

691
00:42:53.166 --> 00:42:54.291
[Rachel sighs]

692
00:42:55.166 --> 00:42:56.166
[Ray] Come on.

693
00:43:03.250 --> 00:43:04.666
[rustling]

694
00:43:04.750 --> 00:43:07.458
[suspenseful music building]

695
00:43:16.291 --> 00:43:17.458
[device whirs]

696
00:43:21.791 --> 00:43:23.541
[music fades]

697
00:43:23.625 --> 00:43:24.916
[door squeaks softly]

698
00:43:30.375 --> 00:43:31.458
[bag rustles]

699
00:43:48.166 --> 00:43:49.625
[man 1 yells]

700
00:43:49.708 --> 00:43:52.208
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [both grunting]

701
00:43:55.208 --> 00:43:56.583
[gunshots]

702
00:44:01.458 --> 00:44:02.958
- [blade clicks]
- [Ray groans]

703
00:44:03.791 --> 00:44:05.000
[knife clatters]

704
00:44:05.916 --> 00:44:07.583
[man 1 choking and grunting]

705
00:44:14.875 --> 00:44:15.875
[neck snaps]

706
00:44:17.291 --> 00:44:18.666
[Ray grunts. panting]

707
00:44:24.833 --> 00:44:25.833
[gunshot]

708
00:44:31.083 --> 00:44:32.208
[grunts]

709
00:44:34.416 --> 00:44:35.958
[music building]

710
00:44:39.625 --> 00:44:40.916
[door unlocks]

711
00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:42.416
[gunfire]

712
00:44:42.500 --> 00:44:43.666
[door slams]

713
00:44:44.791 --> 00:44:45.916
[music dies down]

714
00:44:54.416 --> 00:44:56.416
[man 2 panting]

